    {"children":[{"checked":null,"children":[{"children":[{"children":[{"type":"text","value":"天空中有云"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","value":" (tiānkōng zhōng yǒu yún) - \"there are clouds in the sky\""}],"type":"paragraph"}],"spread":false,"type":"listItem"},{"checked":null,"children":[{"children":[{"children":[{"type":"text","value":"乌云"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","value":" (wūyún) - \"dark clouds\""}],"type":"paragraph"}],"spread":false,"type":"listItem"},{"checked":null,"children":[{"children":[{"children":[{"type":"text","value":"云层"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","value":" (yúncéng) - \"cloud layer\""}],"type":"paragraph"}],"spread":false,"type":"listItem"},{"checked":null,"children":[{"children":[{"children":[{"type":"text","value":"风云"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","value":" (fēngyún) - \"wind and clouds; changing situation\""}],"type":"paragraph"}],"spread":false,"type":"listItem"},{"checked":null,"children":[{"children":[{"children":[{"type":"text","value":"云端"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","value":" (yúnduān) - \"cloud top; the cloud (computing)\""}],"type":"paragraph"}],"spread":false,"type":"listItem"}],"ordered":false,"spread":false,"start":null,"type":"list"},
    {"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Cultural Context"}],"depth":2,"type":"heading"},
    {"children":[{"type":"text","value":"云 carries rich symbolic meaning in Chinese culture, representing both the physical phenomenon and\nabstract concepts of change, mystery, and transcendence. In traditional Chinese art and poetry,\nclouds symbolize the ethereal realm between earth and heaven, often associated with immortals and\nspiritual ascension. The phrase \"行云流水\" (xíng yún liú shuǐ) - \"flowing clouds and running\nwater\" - describes natural, effortless movement. In modern times, 云 has gained new significance in\ntechnology, representing distributed computing and digital connectivity."}],"type":"paragraph"}
